LogFile.FinalText: Some people claim men and women speak different languages. In a couple, if a men says that he does not want to speak about his own problems, the typical women feels excluded from his world. If the women tells him that she does not want to discuss the problems, most men thinks that she does not have a need to talk about the issues. These types of misunderstandings may give rise to arguments. When big arguments occur, women and men also reacts differently. New research shows that many women cry when they get angry. In such situations, frightened men choose to escape, and they may feel helpless. Contrary to the crying woman, angry men use harsh words. Despite their different reactions, most men and women live peacefully together, and we probably cannot live without eachother.
